premise_source_doc_sentence: Kleptocracy  (  from Ancient Greek κλέπτης  (  kléptēs , `` thief ''  )  , κλέπτω  (  kléptō , `` steal ''  )  , from Proto-Indo-European * klep -  (  `` to steal ''  )  ; and from the Ancient Greek suffix - κρατία  (  - kratía  )  , from κράτος  (  krátos , `` power , rule '' ; klépto - thieves + - kratos rule , literally `` rule by thieves ''  )  is a government with corrupt leaders  (  kleptocrats  )  that use their power to exploit the people and natural resources of their own territory in order to extend their personal wealth and political power .
